6e11a3d4-bc47-47ca-be15-f881bf50c546.0ffa7ec1-9c4a-4a25-ab90-1cbee008d0c2.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex (The values are not case sensitive)
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
6e11a3d4-bc47-47ca-be15-f881bf50c546.42e1cba0-eea4-4962-8fee-91344881bd8d.description=
This operation iterates through a list of values. It is not recommended to modify the value of the "list" and "separator" inputs during the iteration process.

Inputs\:
    list - The list to iterate through.
    separator - A delimiter separating the list elements.
Default value\: ‘,’ (comma) 

Results\:
    resultString - The current list element (if the response is "has more").

Responses\:
    has more - Another value was found in the list and it has been returned.
    no more - The iterator has gone through the entire list. This response is returned once per list iteration.  A subsequent call to the List iterator operation restarts the list iteration process.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Note\:
   The position of the iterator in the list is tracked by each step's unique identifier. Therefore, you can simultaneously iterate through the same list from multiple steps.

Outputs\: assetTag - The server's asset tag. beginDate - The date when the server was first discovered or when its OS was last provisioned. chassisID - The server's chassis identifier. hardwareSignature - The server's hardware signature. manufacturer - The server's manufacturer. model - The server's model. serialNumber - The server's serial number. uuid - The server's UUID. interfacesType - The types of the server's network interfaces, separated by 'separator'. interfacesHardwareAddress - The hardware addresses of the server's network interfaces, separated by 'separator'. interfacesIPAddress - The IP addresses, in dotted decimal notation, of the server's network interfaces, separated by 'separator'. interfacesNetmask - The netmasks, in dotted decimal notation, of the server's network interfaces, separated by 'separator'. storagesType - The types of the server's storage components, separated by 'separator'. storagesCapacity - The capacities, in megabytes, of the server's storage components, separated by 'separator'. storagesModel - The device model informations of the server's storage components, separated by 'separator'. storagesDrive - The drives where the server's storage components are mapped, separated by 'separator'. memoriesType - The types of the server's memory components, separated by 'separator'. Types can be either SWAP or RAM. memoriesQuantity - The quantities, in kilobytes, of the server's memory components, separated by 'separator'. cpusModel - The models of the server's CPUs, separated by 'separator'. cpusSpeed - The speeds, in MHz, of the server's CPUs, separated by 'separator'. cpusFamily - The families of the server's CPUs, separated by 'separator'. cpusPhysicalCoresCount - The physical core numbers of the server's CPU's, separated by 'separator'. Available only from SA version 10.1 (sas101). cpusLogicalCoresCount - The logical core numbers of the server's CPU's, separated by 'separator'. Available only from SA version 10.1 (sas101). virtualizationType - The server's virtualization type. rack - The server's rack location. enclosure - The server's enclosure. bay - The server's bay.
